Wendy and her team at Thermo King are advancing their document processing and Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) capabilities and are now entering a more complex, second phase of maturity. After initial progress, including a significant improvement from switching their PDF processing approach, they are expanding to handle a broader set of document types (PDFs, Excel, PowerPoint, Word) and building systems to ingest, structure, and retrieve information effectively. While early guidance helped establish a strong foundation, the team is now encountering more nuanced challenges around how to architect pipelines for diverse document sets, optimize retrieval quality, and scale their approach across varying formats and use cases.

At this stage, Wendy is seeking deeper, expert-level support to navigate key strategic and technical decisions, particularly around how to balance generalized versus highly specific processing, how to structure “golden datasets” for evaluation, and how to extract meaningful, actionable insights from unstructured content. Beyond technical implementation, there is a growing need to align on what “good” looks like in terms of performance and business value. She is looking to engage with practitioners who have hands-on experience managing complex document ecosystems to provide best practices, refine their approach, and help ensure their RAG efforts translate into impactful, scalable outcomes for the business.
